dialogue: Get over here.
We follow behind them urgently...
We have an important customer inside; furnished him a two-story office space downtown on the cheap last year. He's interested in us doing some built-in work at a residence.
Mr. Van Buren, this is my cousin, Laszlo.
Please - that's what people call my father. Call me Harry.
Harry would like some shelving units installed over at his family's property in Doylestown.
Sorry to interrupt.
I hoped someone might follow me out there to take a look at my father's study. My sister and I'd like to surprise him by turning it into a proper library.
We can make you something like that. Let me have Audrey come down to keep an eye on the place. I'll pull the van around.
Fantastic.
They've got something like nine hundred acres out here, I'm not kidding. A few buildings downtown too- one of them's a department store.
Stay left until you see the main house. You can park wherever you'd like.
ATTILA turns his clumsy green Bedford through the front gates.
I do appreciate you coming out here on such short notice, gentlemen. Father's away only until next Friday so I was anxious to pin this down.
It's no inconvenience for us, chief.
It's your lucky day too cause my cousin here is a licensed architect, and a specialist in renovations... He's even designed a library before, back at home. I mean, a whole city library.
What city is that?
What's your budget?
What's your estimate?
Don't worry, we'll come in on- budget. You want this all done by next Friday, you said?
Thursday night, preferably. I can't be here during the week but the staff can let you in, and if anything comes up, have them ring me at the office.
